0judges%20keep%20ruling%20against%20President%20Trump%2C%20but%20they%20have%20no%20real%20power%20to%20enforce%20their%20decisions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20president%20has%20much%20more%20force%20at%20his%20disposal%20than%20do%20the%20courts%2C%26quot%3B%20Cornell%20Law%20School%20professor%20Michael%20Dorf%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20despite%20a%20federal%20court%20order%20Monday%20barring%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-musk-doge-timeline-federal-workforce-2025-2%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eadministration's%20spending%20freeze%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20numerous%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%20programs%20remain%20inaccessible%20to%20their%20intended%20recipients.%20US%20District%20Judge%20John%20McConnell%20said%20state%20agencies%20have%20a%20%26quot%3Brightful%20concern%26quot%3B%20that%20they%20still%20couldn't%20access%20some%20programs.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EConstitutional%20law%20experts%20warn%20that%20if%20a%20president%20chose%20to%20defy%20court%20orders%2C%20judges%20would%20have%20limited%20options.%20The%20consequences%20would%20likely%20fall%20on%20lower-level%20officials%2C%20not%20the%20president%20himself%2C%20said%20Michael%20J.%20Gerhardt%2C%20a%20constitutional%20law%20professor%20at%20the%20University%20of%20North%20Carolina%20School%20of%20Law%20in%20Chapel%20Hill.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20the%20very%20least%2C%20you%20would%20have%20a%20possible%20contempt%20citation%20directed%20at%20a%20particular%20official%20who%20has%20refused%20to%20comply%20with%20a%20court%20order%2C%26quot%3B%20Gerhardt%20told%20BI%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20they%20indicate%20they%20are%20defying%20it%20because%20of%20his%20order%2C%20then%20the%20court%20is%20going%20to%20include%20the%20president%20in%20the%20citation%20of%20contempt.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20enforcing%20even%20that%20would%20fall%20to%20the%20Justice%20Department%20%E2%80%94%20which%20answers%20to%20Tru