%20considered%20by%20Trump%20administration%20may%20hit%20Indians%20on%20green%20card%20queues%20hard%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1738923790000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-118013823%2Cimgsize-664928.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fimmigration-policy-changes-being-considered-by-trump-administration-may-hit-indians-on-green-card-queues-hard%2Farticleshow%2F118013429.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F118013429.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EThe%20Trump%20administration's%20potential%20policy%20changes%2C%20including%20the%20revocation%20of%20birthright%20citizenship%20and%20employment%20authorisation%20documents%20for%20H-4%20visa%20holders%2C%20raise%20concerns%20for%20Indian%20H-1B%20visa%20professionals.%20These%20changes%20could%20exacerbate%20the%20green%20card%20backlog%2C%20increase%20the%20number%20of%20'aging-out'%20children%2C%20and%20cause%20financial%20instability.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Ishani%20Duttagupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fimmigration-policy-changes-being-considered-by-trump-administration-may-hit-indians-on-green-card-queues-hard%2Farticleshow%2F118013429.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fimmigration-policy-changes-being-considered-by-trump-administration-may-hit-indians-on-green-card-queues-hard%2Famp_articleshow%2F118013429.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fimmigration-policy-changes-being-considered-by-trump-administration-may-hit-indians-on-green-card-queues-hard%2Famp_articleshow%2F118013429.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20India%20Became%20Home%20to%2075%25%20of%20the%20World%E2%80%99s%20Tigers%20by%20Doubling%20Their%20Numbers%20in%2010%20Years%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EGood%20news%20for%20India%20%E2%80%94%20tigers%20are%20making%20a%20big%20comeback!%20According%20to%20a%20new%20study%20in%20the%20journal%20%3Cem%3EScience%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20in%20just%20over%20ten%20years%2C%20India%20has%20doubled%20its%20number%20of%20tigers.%20Now%20there%20are%20more%20than%203%2C600%20tigers%20living%20there.%20This%20means%20three%20out%20of%20every%20four%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F343739%2Fhuman-animal-tiger-conflict-in-chandrapur-maharashtra-reduced-with-ai-tech-wildlife-eye-innovation-valiance%2F%23google_vignette%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ewild%20tigers%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20world%20live%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20makes%20this%20really%20special%3F%20These%20tigers%20live%20in%20an%20area%20that%E2%80%99s%20just%20half%20the%20size%20of%20Britain%2C%20and%20they%20share%20this%20space%20with%2060%20million%20people.%20That%E2%80%99s%20a%20lot%20of%20humans%20and%20tigers%20living%20near%20each%20other!%20The%20research%20team%20found%20that%20this%20special%20area%20covers%20about%201%2C38%2C200%20square%20kilometres%20of%20land%2C%20where%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F338189%2Fbest-national-park-wildlife-safaris-in-winter-adventure-travel-guide-vacation%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Etigers%20roam%20freely%3C%2Fa%3E%20through%20forests%2C%20grasslands%2C%20and%20even%20areas%20close%20to%20villages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3EThe%20study%20credits%20four%20core%20areas%20that%20helped%20India%20achieve%20this%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cul%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-list%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIndia%20was%20able%20to%20stop%20people%20from%20hunting%20tigers%20by%20having%20strict%20laws%20and%20forest%20guards%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIndia%20protected%20the%20places%20where%20tigers%20live%20by%20making%20special%20areas%20called%20reserves%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20country%20made%20sure%20tigers%20had%20enough%20food%20to%20eat%20by%20protecting%20deer%20and%20other%20animals%20that%20tigers%20hunt%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIndia%20helped%20the%20people%20who%20live%20near%20tigers%20by%20giving%20them%20support%20and%20money%20if%20and%20when%20they%20faced%20problems%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYadvendradev%20Vikramsinh%20Jhala%2C%20the%20study%E2%80%99s%20lead%20author%2C%20told%20the%20%3Cem%3EBBC%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20think%20human%20densities%20are%20detrimental%20to%20conservation%20of%20large%20carnivores.%20But%20more%20than%20density%2C%20it%20is%20the%20attitude%20of%20people%20that%20matters.%E2%80%9D%20He%20pointed%20out%20that%20despite%20having%20a%20lower%20population%20density%2C%20Malaysia%20has%20not%20successfully%20revived%20its%20tiger%20population%20due%20to%20different%20socio-economic%20and%20conservation%20approaches.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Clabel%3EAdvertisement%3C%2Flabel%3E%5Cn%3Cins%20data-ad-slot%3D%5C%222400846096%5C%22%20data-ad-client%3D%5C%22ca-pub-5691287967087057%5C%22%20data-ad-format%3D%5C%22fluid%5C%22%20data-ad-layout%3D%5C%22in-article%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2020%2F07%2F23140155%2Ftiger-watch-4.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Tiger%20Family%20Having%20Fun%20in%20the%20Wild%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-233474%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ETigers%20have%20adapted%20to%20landscapes%20shared%20by%20nearly%2060%20million%20people%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20some%20parts%20of%20India%2C%20like%20Madhya%20Pradesh%20and%20Karnataka%2C%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%2